20Arabi%20Baptist%20hospital.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EBut%20what%20is%20the%20Islamic%20Jihad%20group%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Beginnings%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%20%3Cp%3EDesignated%20as%20a%20terrorist%20organisation%20by%20the%20US%20State%20Department%2C%20the%20Palestinian%20Islamic%20Jihad%20(PIJ)%2C%20an%20ally%20of%20Hamas%2C%20violently%20opposes%20the%20existence%20of%20Israel.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20group's%20founders%2C%20Fathi%20Shaqaqi%20and%20Abd%20al-Aziz%20Awda%2C%20were%20students%20in%20Egypt%20and%20members%20of%20the%20Egyptian%20Muslim%20Brotherhood%2C%20a%20Sunni%20Islamist%20social%20movement%20founded%20by%20Hassan%20al-Banna%20in%201928.%20Sometime%20in%20the%20late%201970s%20the%20two%20felt%20that%20the%20Brotherhood%20was%20not%20fully%20committed%20to%20the%20Palestinian%20cause.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ETaking%20inspiration%20from%20Ayatollah%20Ruhollah%20Khomeini-led%20Iranian%20revolution%2C%20Shaqaqi%20and%20Awda%20created%20an%20offshoot%20group%20with%20the%20sole%20objective%20of%20militant%20destruction%20of%20the%20Israeli%20state.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%201981%2C%20the%20Egyptian%20government%20exiled%20PIJ%2C%20which%20had%20split%20from%20the%20Muslim%20Brotherhood%2C%20to%20Gaza%20after%20the%20assassination%20of%20President%20Anwar%20Sadat%20in%201981.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EOperations%20In%20Gaza%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20PIJ%20functions%20as%20a%20decentralised%2C%20compartmentalised%20organisation%20that%20typically%20prioritises%20attacking%20Israel%2C%20while%20avoiding%20the%20prominent%20social%2C%20welfare%2C%20and%20political%20roles%20played%20by%20other%20Islamic%20extremist%20groups%20in%20the%20region%20like%20Hamas%2C%20Fatah%2C%20or%20even%20the%20Lebanon-based%20Iran-backed%20group%20Hezbollah.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ETheir%20first%20successful%20strike%20is%20thought%20to%20have%20been%20in%20Gaza%2C%20the%20killing%20of%20an%20Israeli%20military%20police%20captain%20in%20August%201987%2C%20a%20few%20months%20before%20the%20first%20Palestinian%20intifada.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWhile%20in%20Gaza%2C%20the%20Islamic%20Jihad%20killed%20an%20Israeli%20military%20police%20captain%20just%20a%20few%20months%20before%20the%20start%20of%20the%20First%20Intifada%20in%201987.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20same%20year%2C%20they%20were%20expelled%20to%20Lebanon%20where%20the%20Islamic%20Jihad%20built%20a%20strong%20relationship%20with%20Hezbollah%20and%20even%20received%20arms%20training%20from%20Iranian%20Revolutionary%20Guards.%20Two%20years%20later%2C%20Shaqaqi%20established%20the%20group's%20official%20headquarters%20in%20Syria's%20Damascus%20where%20they%20continue%20to%20operate%20to%20this%20day.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ERelationship%20With%20Hamas%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%20%3Cp%3EUnlike%20Hamas%2C%20the%20Islamic%20Jihad%20does%20not%20carry%20out%20any%20form%20of%20social%20service%20in%20Gaza%20nor%20does%20it%20intend%20to%20fight%20for%20political%20office%20or%20intend%20to%20open%20diplomatic%20channels%20with%20Israel.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20one%20thing%20that%20is%20common%20between%20the%20two%20groups%20is%20the%20fact%20that%20both%20oppose%20Israel.%20Hamas%20and%20Islamic%20Jihad%20have%20often%20coordinated%20militant%20operations%20in%20the%20Palestinian%20enclave.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20there%20have%20been%20times%20when%20Hamas%2C%20ironically%2C%20has%20cautioned%20the%20Islamic%20Jihad%20against%20attacking%20Israel.%20The%20Islamic%20Jihad%2C%20on%20most%20occasions%2C%20acts%20independently.%20Primarily%20focused%20on%20military%20confrontations%2C%20there%20have%20been%20times%20when%20the%20Islamic%20Jihad%20has%20taken%20the%20front%20seat%20while%20Hamas%20remained%20on%20the%20sidelines%20during%20clashes%20with%20Israel.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ERelationship%20With%20Iran%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20Iranian%20Revolution's%20sphere%20of%20influence%20in%20its%20first%20decade%20was%20confined%20to%20Shi'a%20groups%20in%20Iraq%2C%20Lebanon%2C%20and%20the%20Gulf%20Emirates.%20It%20failed%20to%20make%20headways%20in%20countries%20with%20a%20majority%20Sunni%20population%20nor%20did%20its%20fundamentalist%20ideas%20entice%20Islamic%20militant%20groups.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWhile%20Shaqaqi%20and%20Awda%20drew%20inspiration%20from%20the%20Iranian%20Revolution%2C%20Iran%20did%20not%20pay%20it%20any%20heed.%20Ayatollah%20Khomenei%20and%20Iranian%20leaders%20remained%20steadfast%20in%20propagating%20Shi'ite%20values%20without%20focusing%20on%20Sunni-dominated%20nations.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20a%20change%20occurred.%20In%20the%20late%2080s%2C%20after%20the%20end%20of%20the%20Iran-Iraq%20War%2C%20Iran%20decided%20to%20export%20its%20fundamentalism%20to%20countries%20like%20Egypt%2C%20Tunisia%2C%20Sudan%2C%20and%20more%20importantly%2C%20Palestine%20--%20coinciding%20with%20the%20First%20Intifada.%20And%20after%20Israel%20kicked%20the%20Islamic%20Jihad%20to%20Lebanon%2C%20the%20group%20came%20under%20direct%20influence%20of%20Iran.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20US%20State%20Department%2C%20it%20is%20Iran%20that%20funds%20the%20Islamic%20Jihad's%20budget%2C%20exactly%20like%20it%20reportedly%20does%20for%20Hamas%20and%20Hezbollah.%20The%20US%20also%20blames%20the%20Bashar%20al-Assad%20regime%20in%20Syria%20for%20providing%20a%20safe%20haven%20to%20the%20group%20in%20Damascus.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EAttacks%20Carried%20Out%20By%20Islamic%20Jihad%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20Islamic%20Jihad's%20modus%20operandi%20includes%20suicide%20bombings%20targetting%20Israeli%20civilians%20and%20military%20personnel.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E1987%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3A%20Killing%20Of%20an%20Israeli%20military%20police%20commander%20in%20Gaza%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E1994%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3A%20Car%20bomb%20attack%20killing%20nine%20and%20injuring%2050%20aboard%20a%20public%20bus%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E1995%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3A%20Suicide%20bomb%20attack%20killing%2018%20soldiers%20and%20one%20civilian%20in%20ISrael's%20Netanya.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E1996%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3A%20Suicide%20bomb%20attack%20at%20a%20Tel%20Aviv%20shopping%20mall%20killing%2013%20and%20injuring%2075.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E2003%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3A%20Suicide%20bomb%20attack%20a%20a%20Haifa%20restaurant%20killing%2022%20and%20injuring%2060.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAlong%20with%20other%20suicide%20bombings%2C%20the%20Islamic%20Jihad%20also%20works%20with%20Hamas%20to%20launch%20rockets%20into%20Israel.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1697611320000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-10%2F30usstlg_gaza-hospital-reuters-_625x300_18_October_23.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fisrael-gaza-palestine-hamas-explained-what-is-islamic-jihad-group-blamed-by-israel-for-gaza-hospital-bombing-4491459%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Israel%20Gaza%20War%3A%20Designated%20as%20a%20terrorist%20organisation%20by%20the%20US%20State%20Department%2C%20the%20Palestinian%20Islamic%20Jihad%20(PIJ)%2C%20an%20ally%20of%20Hamas%2C%20violently%20opposes%20the%20existence%20of%20Israel.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fisrael-gaza-palestine-hamas-explained-what-is-islamic-jihad-group-blamed-by-israel-for-gaza-hospital-bombing-4491459%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fisrael-gaza-palestine-hamas-explained-what-is-islamic-jihad-group-blamed-by-israel-for-gaza-hospital-bombing-4491459%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fisrael-gaza-palestine-hamas-explained-what-is-islamic-jihad-group-blamed-by-israel-for-gaza-hospital-bombing-4491459%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Explained%3A%20What's%20At%20Stake%20For%20Egypt%20As%20Israel%20Fights%20Hamas%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EAs%20the%20Israeli-Hamas%20crisis%20continues%2C%20a%20great%20deal%20of%20focus%20is%20shifting%20to%20Egypt.%20Egypt%20shares%20a%20border%20with%20both%20Israel%20and%20Gaza%20%E2%80%93%20the%20narrow%20strip%20of%20Palestinian%20territory%20which%20is%20currently%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amnesty.org%2Fen%2Flatest%2Fnews%2F2023%2F10%2Fisrael-opt-israel-must-lift-illegal-and-inhumane-blockade-on-gaza-as-power-plant-runs-out-of-fuel%2F%5C%22%3Eunder%20blockade%3C%2Fa%3E%20following%20the%20violent%20attack%20against%20Israel%20by%20Hamas%2C%20a%20radical%20Islamist%20organisation%20that%20has%20controlled%20Gaza%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.com%2Fnews%2Fworld-middle-east-67039975%5C%22%3Esince%202007%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EMoina%20Spooner%2C%20from%20The%20Conversation%20Africa%2C%20asked%20Ofir%20Winter%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.inss.org.il%2Fperson%2Fwinterofir%2F%5C%22%3Ewho%20studies%3C%2Fa%3E%20Egyptian%20politics%20and%20the%20Arab-Israeli%20conflict%2C%20to%20provide%20insights%20into%20what%20the%20new%20war%20means%20for%20Egypt%20and%20the%20role%20it%20plays.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat's%20been%20the%20relationship%20between%20Egypt%20and%20Israel%20and%20Palestine%20in%20the%20past%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%20%3Cp%3EEgypt%20performs%20a%20balancing%20act%20in%20managing%20relations%20between%20Israel%20and%20Palestine.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EEgypt%20openly%20expresses%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fenglish.aawsat.com%2Farab-world%2F4598426-sisi-egypt-won%25E2%2580%2599t-allow-termination-palestinian-cause-expense-other-parties%5C%22%3Eits%20commitment%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20the%20Palestinian%20cause.%20This%20is%20because%20Palestine's%20quest%20for%20self-determination%20is%20a%20central%20Arab%20and%20Islamic%20cause.%20Also%2C%20due%20to%20geographical%20proximity%2C%20any%20escalation%20in%20Gaza%20will%20have%20a%20direct%20impact%20on%20Egypt's%20national%20interests.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThis%20position%20is%20reflected%20in%20its%20reaction%20to%20the%20outbreak%20of%20violence%20between%20Israel%20and%20Hamas.%20Following%20the%20deadly%20killings%20and%20kidnappings%20of%20innocent%20Israeli%20civilians%20by%20Hamas%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fapnews.com%2Farticle%2Fisrael-palestinians-gaza-hamas-rockets-airstrikes-tel-aviv-11fb98655c256d54ecb5329284fc37d2%5C%22%3Eearlier%20this%20month%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Egyptian%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fenglish.ahram.org.eg%2FNewsContent%2F1%2F1234%2F510287%2FEgypt%2FForeign-Affairs%2FEgyptian-MPs-condemn-Israeli-aggression-on-Gaza%2C-s.aspx%5C%22%3Emembers%20of%20parliament%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fwatch%3Fv%3DW3sDlhRckI0%5C%22%3Estate-owned%20media%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20have%20portrayed%20Israel%20as%20the%20aggressor%20and%20Hamas%20as%20the%20victim.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20accordance%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.aljazeera.com%2Fnews%2F2022%2F4%2F26%2Fegypts-role-gaza-more-than-mediator%5C%22%3Epast%20actions%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Egypt%20can%20be%20expected%20to%20take%20several%20steps%20to%20demonstrate%20its%20solidarity%20with%20the%20Palestinians.%20These%20include%3B%20the%20provision%20of%20humanitarian%20assistance%20to%20Gaza%2C%20evacuation%20of%20some%20wounded%20to%20Egyptian%20hospitals%2C%20and%20increased%20role%20in%20mediation%20efforts%20for%20a%20ceasefire.%20These%20steps%20make%20Egypt%20a%20key%20actor%20in%20the%20conflict%20and%20would%20help%20strengthen%20its%20regional%20and%20international%20standing.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20Egypt%20also%20doesn't%20want%20to%20alienate%20Israel.%20Ultimately%2C%20they%20have%20a%20mutual%20interest%3A%20they%20do%20not%20want%20to%20see%20the%20resurgence%20of%20political%20Islam%20in%20the%20region.%20This%20is%20linked%20to%20Egypt's%20own%20experience%20of%20Islamist%20organisations.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20current%20regime%20in%20Egypt%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2013%2F07%2F04%2Fworld%2Fmiddleeast%2Fegypt.html%5C%22%3Eousted%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20Muslim%20Brotherhood%20in%202013%20and%20outlawed%20them.%20The%20Brotherhood%20is%20a%20transnational%20Islamist%20organisation%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cfr.org%2Fbackgrounder%2Fegypts-muslim-brotherhood%5C%22%3Efounded%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20Egypt%20in%201928.%20It's%20aims%20are%20to%20promote%20social%20and%20political%20change%20in%20Muslim-majority%20countries.%20After%20the%20Arab%20Spring%20in%202011%2C%20the%20Brotherhood%20held%20power%20in%20Egypt%20for%20one%20year%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.aljazeera.com%2Fnews%2F2012%2F6%2F24%2Fcelebration-in-egypt-as-morsi-declared-winner%5C%22%3Ebefore%20being%20ousted%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHamas%20is%20an%20offspring%20of%20the%20Muslim%20Brotherhood%2C%20which%20is%20why%20Egypt%20perceives%20it%20as%20a%20threat.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EBut%20despite%20Egypt's%20suspicious%20approach%20to%20Hamas%2C%20since%202017%20there's%20been%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.inss.org.il%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2018%2F01%2FGazaCrisis_ENG-129-140.pdf%5C%22%3Ean%20understanding%3C%2Fa%3E%20between%20the%20two%3A%20Hamas'%20cooperation%20in%20fighting%20terrorism%20in%20Sinai%20would%20be%20met%20with%20an%20easing%20of%20the%20Egyptian%20blockade%20on%20Gaza.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThough%20the%20relations%20between%20Egypt%20and%20Israel%20are%20cooperative%2C%20they're%20not%20warm.%20Egypt%20signed%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fhistory.state.gov%2Fmilestones%2F1977-1980%2Fcamp-david%5C%22%3Epeace%20agreement%20with%20Israel%20in%201979%3C%2Fa%3E.%20And%2C%20over%20the%20past%20decade%2C%20Israel%20has%20positioned%20itself%20as%20a%20key%20political%2C%20security%20and%20economic%20partner%20to%20Egypt.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20recent%20years%2C%20Egypt%20has%20been%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcarnegieendowment.org%2Fsada%2F85037%5C%22%3Emediator%3C%2Fa%3E%20between%20Israel%20and%20Hamas%20and%20in%20the%20reconstruction%20efforts%20of%20Gaza.%20This%20is%20because%20of%20its%20proximity%20to%20Gaza%20and%20the%20fact%20that%20it%20controls%20the%20Rafah%20crossing%20%E2%80%93%20the%20only%20border%20with%20the%20Gaza%20strip%20that's%20not%20under%20Israeli%20control.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EBut%20Egypt's%20involvement%20with%20Gaza%20has%20certain%20lines%20that%20won't%20be%20crossed.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThere%20will%20be%20no%20Egyptian%20military%20involvement%20against%20Israel%20for%20the%20benefit%20of%20the%20Palestinians%20%E2%80%93%20a%20policy%20which%20primarily%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.state.gov%2Fsecretary-antony-j-blinken-and-egyptian-president-abdel-fattah-el-sisi-before-their-meeting%2F%5C%22%3Ederives%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20Egypt's%20commitment%20to%20the%201979%20peace%20agreement%20between%20Israel%20and%20Egypt.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThere%20will%20also%20be%20no%20sanctioned%20mass%20entry%20of%20Gazans%20into%20Egypt%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsis.gov.eg%2FStory%2F187293%2FSisi-Palestinians-must-%2527remain-on-their-land%2527%252C-contacts-ongoing-for-de-escalation-in-Gaza-war%3Flang%3Den-us%5C%22%3Eaccording%20to%3C%2Fa%3E%20declarations%20by%20President%20Abdel%20Fattah%20el-Sisi%20and%20other%20Egyptian%20officials.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EHow%20does%20the%20current%20crisis%20affect%20Egypt%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%20%3Cp%3EEgypt%20has%20so%20far%20rejected%20the%20idea%20of%20displaced%20Palestinians%20moving%20into%20Sinai.%20But%20there%20is%20the%20possibility%20that%20a%20large%20number%20of%20Gazans%20will%20seek%20entry.%20This%20is%20separate%20to%20the%20Gaza%20residents%20with%20foreign%20citizenship%20who%20are%20already%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.com%2Fnews%2Flive%2Fworld-middle-east-67119233%5C%22%3Ewaiting%20at%20the%20border%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20cross.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EEgypt%20is%20against%20allowing%20Gazans%20crossing%20the%20border%20in%20large%20numbers%20because%20it%20opposes%20any%20encroachment%20on%20its%20sovereignty%20in%20the%20Sinai%20Peninsula.%20Its%20major%20concern%20is%20that%20displaced%20Palestinians%20may%20establish%20a%20permanent%20residence%20in%20its%20territory%2C%20potentially%20undermining%20the%20already%20delicate%20security%20and%20economic%20situation.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20situation%20also%20poses%20a%20large%20security%20risk%20to%20Egypt.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EFirst%2C%20border%20breaches%20by%20refugees%20from%20Gaza%2C%20some%20of%20whom%20may%20be%20armed%20individuals%20affiliated%20with%20Hamas%20or%20other%20radical%20groups%2C%20could%20export%20instability%20to%20Sinai.%20For%20Egypt%2C%20there%20is%20a%20danger%20that%20there%20could%20be%20more%20terrorist%20attacks%20and%20instability%20as%20there%20were%20in%20Sinai%20before%20the%202017%20understanding%20with%20Hamas.%20Some%20of%20those%20attacks%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.euromesco.net%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2018%2F02%2FEuroMeSCo36-Geopolitics-of-Violent-Extremism.-The-Case-of-Sinai.pdf%5C%22%3Ewere%20carried%20out%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20well-armed%20and%20trained%20Gaza-based%20militant%20cells.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ESecond%2C%20a%20massive%20blow%20to%20Hamas%20may%20lead%20to%20a%20lack%20of%20governance%2C%20chaos%2C%20and%20instability%20in%20Gaza.%20This%20will%20cause%20instability%20and%20could%20give%20rise%20to%20the%20smuggling%20of%20weapons%20and%20fighters%20along%20Egypt's%20border%20with%20the%20Gaza%20Strip.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20other%20security%20threat%20is%20that%20terrorist%20acts%20could%20be%20launched%20from%20Sinai%20into%20Israel%20by%20Palestinian%20militant%20groups%20putting%20the%20delicate%20relationship%20between%20Israel%20and%20Egypt%20at%20risk.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EHow%20has%20Egypt%20reacted%20and%20what%20should%20it%20do%20next%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%20%3Cp%3ESince%20the%20outbreak%20of%20the%20war%2C%20Egypt%20has%20been%20working%20to%20de-escalate%20the%20situation%20in%20Gaza%20and%20has%20been%20conducting%20talks%20with%20Israel%2C%20Hamas%2C%20the%20Palestinian%20Authority%2C%20the%20US%2C%20Iran%2C%20and%20other%20regional%20and%20international%20players.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20Arab%20League%20has%20already%20convened%20in%20Cairo%2C%20and%20an%20international%20conference%20in%20Egypt%20is%20expected%20to%20take%20place%20this%20weekend.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.aljazeera.com%2Fnews%2F2023%2F10%2F16%2Fegypts-tricky-calculation-as-israels-assault-on-gaza-continues%5C%22%3EEgypt%20is%20also%20seeking%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20establish%20a%20humanitarian%20corridor%20for%20the%20delivery%20of%20food%20and%20medicine%20to%20the%20Gaza%20Strip.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAt%20this%20stage%2C%20Egypt%20has%20more%20control%20than%20most%20other%20regional%20international%20players%20over%20the%20outcomes%20of%20the%20conflict%2C%20as%20well%20as%20plenty%20of%20interests.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20outcome%20of%20the%20conflict%20could%20deliver%20some%20benefits.%20For%20example%2C%20Egypt%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.jpost.com%2Fmiddle-east%2Farticle-745511%5C%22%3Edesires%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20return%20of%20the%20Palestinian%20Authority%2C%20who%20is%20more%20willing%20to%20engage%20in%20diplomacy%20and%20negotiations%2C%20as%20the%20governing%20authority%20in%20Gaza.%20A%20scenario%20where%20Hamas%20is%20significantly%20weakened%20could%20pave%20the%20way%20for%20new%20developments%2C%20possibly%20including%20the%20gradual%20return%20of%20the%20Palestinian%20Authority.%20In%20this%20case%2C%20Egypt%20and%20Israel%20could%20find%20a%20more%20pragmatic%20neighbour%20across%20their%20borders.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIf%20Hamas%20loses%20power%20at%20the%20end%20of%20the%20war%2C%20Egypt%20will%20most%20probably%20be%20involved%20in%20the%20government%20transition%20phase.%20As%20in%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fapnews.com%2Farticle%2Fhamas-abdel-fattah-el-sissi-middle-east-egypt-africa-e016845c51bf45d9652fbe41ed09dab6%5C%22%3Epast%20few%20years%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Egypt%20is%20expected%20to%20be%20the%20conduit%20through%20which%20aid%20and%20funds%20from%20Arab%20countries%20and%20the%20international%20community%20will%20be%20transferred%20into%20Gaza%2C%20participate%20in%20its%20reconstruction%20process%2C%20and%20be%20a%20dominant%20influencing%20factor%20on%20shaping%20its%20future.%3Cimg%20referrerpolicy%3D%5C%22no-referrer-when-downgrade%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcounter.theconversation.com%2Fcontent%2F215710%2Fcount.gif%3Fdistributor%3Drepublish-lightbox-basic%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20Conversation%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheconversation.com%2Fprofiles%2Fofir-winter-1479992%5C%22%3EOfir%20Winter%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Senior%20Researcher%2C%20Institute%20for%20National%20Security%20Studies%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheconversation.com%2Finstitutions%2Ftel-aviv-university-922%5C%22%3ETel%20Aviv%20University%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20article%20is%20republished%20from%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheconversation.com%5C%22%3EThe%20Conversation%3C%2Fa%3E%20under%20a%20Creative%20Commons%20license.%20Read%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheconversation.com%2Fhamas-israeli-conflict-whats-at-stake-for-egypt-215710%5C%22%3Eoriginal%20article%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1697610900000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-10%2F5rn164co_israel-hamas-war_625x300_11_October_23.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fisrael-gaza-hamas-palestine-explained-whats-at-stake-for-egypt-as-israel-fights-hamas-4491580%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22As%20the%20Israeli-Hamas%20crisis%20continues%2C%20a%20great%20deal%20of%20focus%20is%20shifting%20to%20Egypt%20which%20shares%20a%20border%20with%20both%20Israel%20%26amp%3B%20Gaza%20the%20narrow%20strip%20of%20Palestinian%20territory%20which%20is%20currently%20under%20blockade%20following%20the%20violent%20attack%20against%20Israel.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fisrael-gaza-hamas-palestine-explained-whats-at-stake-for-egypt-as-israel-fights-hamas-4491580%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fisrael-gaza-hamas-palestine-explained-whats-at-stake-for-egypt-as-israel-fights-hamas-4491580%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fisrael-gaza-hamas-palestine-explained-whats-at-stake-for-egypt-as-israel-fights-hamas-4491580%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Israel%20Responds%20After%20X%20User%20Asks%20What%20They%20Would%20Eliminate%20From%20The%20World%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EThe%20war%20between%20Israel%20and%20Hamas%20has%20entered%20its%2012th%20day.%20Thousands%20of%20people%20have%20been%20killed%20and%20the%20number%20of%20injured%20is%20going%20up%20each%20day.%20Further%2C%20an%20explosion%20at%20a%20hospital%20in%20Gaza%20killed%20at%20least%20500%20people%20last%20night%2C%20Reuters%20said%20citing%20the%20Hamas-run%20health%20ministry%20sources.%20The%20incident%20has%20sparked%20outrage%20across%20the%20globe.%20Local%20authorities%20blamed%20Israeli%20airstrikes%2C%20while%20Israel%20alleged%20it%20was%20Hamas%20rockets%20misfiring.%20Amid%20the%20ongoing%20conflict%2C%20the%20social%20media%20handles%20of%20Israel%20and%20the%20Israel%20Defence%20Forces%20have%20become%20very%20active%2C%20providing%20information%20and%20updates%20to%20people%20across%20the%20globe.%20The%20State%20of%20Israel's%20official%20X%20account%2C%20in%20response%20to%20a%20user's%20post%2C%20said%20that%20they%20would%20like%20to%20%26quot%3Belimina