20not%20to%20legalise%20marriage%20equality%2C%20and%20instead%20say%20that%20any%20such%20granting%20of%20rights%20had%20to%20be%20done%20by%20the%20executive.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ESeveral%20of%20the%20editorials%20expressed%20the%20opinion%20that%20the%20court%20had%20missed%20an%20opportunity%20to%20end%20existing%20discrimination%2C%20and%20that%20the%20judgment%20comes%20as%20a%20setback%20for%20the%20queer%20community%E2%80%99s%20fight%20for%20rights%20and%20equality.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHere%E2%80%99s%20a%20look%20at%20what%20some%20of%20the%20newspapers%20had%20to%20say.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20Times%20of%20India%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CDo%20same-sex%20couples%20have%20same%20constitutional%20rights%20as%20straight%20couples%3F%20Yes%2C%20should%20have%20been%20SC%E2%80%99s%20answer%2C%E2%80%9D%20%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fblogs%2Ftoi-editorials%2Funtying-the-knot-do-same-sex-couples-have-same-constitutional-rights-as-straight-couples-yes-should-have-been-scs-answer%2F%5C%22%3EThe%20Times%20of%20India%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3Eheadlined%20its%20editorial.%20It%20pointed%20out%20that%20the%20petitioners%20were%20only%20asking%20for%20a%20different%20reading%20of%20the%20Special%20Marriage%20Act%20and%20hence%20access%20to%20legal%20rights%2C%20they%20were%20not%20%E2%80%9Cseeking%20religious%20validation%20or%20social%20approval%20as%20an%20%E2%80%9CIndian%20family%20unit%E2%80%9D%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20right%20to%20equality%20and%20non-discrimination%20means%20that%20LGBT%20citizens%20should%20not%20be%20deprived%20of%20what%20heterosexual%20people%20take%20for%20granted.%20The%20right%20to%20same-sex%20civil%20unions%20should%20have%20flowed%20naturally%20from%20these%20facts%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20newspaper%20stated.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20court%20was%20not%20being%20asked%20to%20intervene%20in%20the%20custom%20of%20marriage%2C%20but%20only%20in%20the%20contract%20with%20rights%20and%20obligations%2C%20as%20it%20is%20laid%20down%20in%20the%20Special%20Marriage%20Act%2C%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Times%20of%20India%3C%2Fem%3E%20said.%20%E2%80%9CSC%E2%80%99s%20core%20job%20is%20to%20uphold%20constitutional%20rights%2C%20irrespective%20of%20popular%20endorsement%20or%20social%20custom.%20It%20could%20have%20affirmed%20constitutional%20principles%2C%20and%20then%20left%20it%20to%20the%20legislature%20to%20do%20its%20job.%20If%20Parliament%20differed%2C%20and%20it%20might%20well%20have%2C%20given%20what%20seems%20to%20be%20the%20prevailing%20political%20opinion%2C%20the%20court%20would%20have%20still%20done%20right%20by%20constitutional%20principles.%20That%20is%20all%20that%20India%E2%80%99s%20sexual%20minorities%20had%20wanted%20from%20the%20country%E2%80%99s%20top%20court.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20Hindu%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Fopinion%2Feditorial%2Flaw-and-custom-on-the-supreme-courts-verdict-on-same-sex-marriage%2Farticle67431076.ece%5C%22%3EThe%20Hindu%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3Ecalled%20the%20court%E2%80%99s%20decision%20a%20%E2%80%9Chuge%20legal%20setback%E2%80%9D%20for%20the%20queer%20community%20in%20India.%20%E2%80%9CIn%20concluding%20that%20there%20is%20no%20fundamental%20right%20to%20marry%2C%20the%20Court%20has%20negated%20the%20expectation%20that%20it%20would%20not%20allow%20discrimination%20against%20same-sex%20couples%20in%20the%20marital%20domain%20to%20continue%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20newspaper%20stated.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CGiven%20that%20large%20sections%20of%20India%20may%20be%20opposed%20to%20the%20legalisation%20of%20same-sex%20marriages%20on%20religious%20and%20cultural%20grounds%2C%20the%20possibility%20of%20Parliament%20taking%20the%20initiative%20to%20do%20so%20is%20quite%20bleak.%20The%20LGBTQIA%2B%20community%20may%20now%20have%20to%20take%20heart%20from%20the%20Court%E2%80%99s%20direction%20that%20the%20government%20should%20form%20a%20committee%20to%20decide%20the%20rights%20and%20entitlements%20of%20queer%20couples.%20The%20community%2C%20however%2C%20still%20has%20quite%20a%20struggle%20ahead%20before%20the%20law%20catches%20up%20with%20its%20yearning%20for%20equality%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20editorial%20concludes.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cem%3EHindustan%20Times%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ESaying%20the%20court%E2%80%99s%20decision%20to%20not%20take%20any%20steps%20at%20all%20in%20the%20direction%20of%20equality%2C%20and%20instead%20leave%20everything%20to%20a%20Union%20government-appointed%20committee%2C%20%E2%80%9Cdisappointing%E2%80%9D%2C%20%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.hindustantimes.com%2Feditorials%2Fholding-back-on-marriage-equality-101697552423579.html%5C%22%3EHindustan%20Times%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3C%2Fem%3Ecalled%20Tuesday%E2%80%99s%20verdict%20a%20setback%20when%20compared%20to%20other%20decisions%20like%20the%20decriminalisation%20of%20same-sex%20relationships.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIn%20every%20country%2C%20the%20journey%20from%20decriminalisation%20of%20queerness%20to%20recognition%20of%20marital%20rights%20has%20been%20long%20and%20arduous.%20So%2C%20granting%20full%20marriage%20rights%20to%20the%20community%20was%20always%20an%20outlier%2C%20especially%20considering%20the%20tangled%20mesh%20of%20secular%20and%20personal%20laws%20that%20govern%20marriage%2C%20divorce%20and%20inheritance%20in%20India.%20But%20the%20court%E2%80%99s%20refusal%20to%20accord%20even%20limited%20recognition%20to%20queer%20couples%20and%20leave%20it%20instead%20to%20executive%20fiat%20is%20disappointing%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20newspaper%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EHindustan%20Times%3C%2Fem%3E%20stated%20that%20the%20struggle%20for%20equal%20rights%20will%20continue%3A%20%E2%80%9C%E2%80%A6in%20the%20long%20arc%20of%20queer%20history%20%E2%80%94%20which%20has%20seen%20the%20top%20court%20dismiss%20a%20community%20as%20a%20%E2%80%9Cminuscule%20minority%E2%80%9D%20only%20to%20say%20history%20owes%20an%20apology%20to%20them%20five%20years%20later%20%E2%80%94%20it%20is%20only%20a%20stumble%2C%20one%20that%20hopefully%20will%20not%20hobble%20the%20quest%20to%20ensure%20a%20life%20of%20dignity%20to%20millions%20of%20Indian%20citizens.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20Indian%20Express%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20court%20did%20not%20provide%20the%20landmark%20judgment%20many%20may%20have%20expected%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Fopinion%2Feditorials%2Fon-marriage-equality-supreme-court-leaves-the-door-ajar-but-fails-to-seize-the-moment-8988025%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20Indian%20Express%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20writes%2C%20its%20recognition%20of%20existing%20discrimination%20%E2%80%9Chas%20opened%20up%20valuable%20room%20for%20finding%20a%20way%20forward%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20court%20did%20not%20go%20far%20enough%20even%20as%20it%20has%20prised%20open%20some%20space%20and%20widened%20the%20room%20for%20manoeuvre%20for%20an%20embattled%20minority.%20Its%20categorical%20no%20to%20same%20sex%20marriage%20can%20also%20be%20said%20to%20make%20many%20of%20its%20empathetic%20observations%20on%20rights%20and%20discrimination%20seem%20like%20tokenism.%20In%20the%20end%2C%20therefore%2C%20the%20verdict%20points%20at%20the%20larger%20battles%20that%20still%20remain%20to%20be%20fought%20%E2%80%93%20the%20necessity%20of%20safeguards%20both%20within%20the%20home%20and%20outside%2C%20the%20recognition%20of%20civil%20unions%20as%20a%20possibility%20for%20the%20community%2C%20and%20the%20realisation%2C%20above%20all%2C%20that%20like%20all%20battles%20for%20equal%20rights%2C%20this%2C%20too%2C%20has%20a%20long%20and%20arduous%20road%20ahead%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20newspaper%20editorial%20stated.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20Tribune%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3