%20from%20the%20researchers'%20study%20explaining%20how%20AI%20models%20could%20accurately%20infer%20personal%20details%20from%20how%20a%20user%20types%2C%20through%20their%20publicly%20available%20information.%3Cp%3ERobin%20Staab%2C%20Mark%20Vero%2C%20Mislav%20Balunovi%C4%87%2C%20Martin%20Vechev%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EOf%20the%20four%20models%20tested%2C%20GPT-4%20was%20the%20most%20accurate%20at%20inferring%20personal%20details%2C%20with%2084.6%25%20accuracy%2C%20per%20the%20study's%20authors.%20Meta's%20Llama2%2C%20Google's%20PalM%2C%20and%20Anthropic's%20Claude%20were%20the%20other%20models%20tested.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20researchers%20also%20found%20that%20Google's%20PalM%20refused%20to%20answer%20around%2010%25%20of%20the%20privacy-invasive%20prompts%20used%20in%20the%20study%20to%20deduce%20personal%20information%20about%20a%20user%2C%20while%20other%20models%20refused%20even%20fewer%20prompts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20not%20even%20clear%20how%20you%20fix%20this%20problem.%20This%20is%20very%2C%20very%20problematic%2C%26quot%3B%20Martin%20Vechev%2C%20a%20professor%20at%20ETH%20Zurich%20and%20one%20of%20the%20study's%20authors%2C%20told%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wired.com%2Fstory%2Fai-chatbots-can-guess-your-personal-information%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EWired%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20an%20article%20published%20Tuesday.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20example%2C%20the%20researchers'%20model%20deduced%20that%20a%20Reddit%20user%20is%20from%20Melbourne%20because%20they%20commented%20about%20a%20%26quot%3Bhook%20turn.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BA%20'hook%20turn'%20is%20a%20traffic%20maneuver%20particularly%20used%20in%20Melbourne%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20GPT-4%20after%20being%20prompted%20to%20identify%20details%20about%20that%20user.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20isn't%20the%20first%20time%20that%20researchers%20have%20identified%20how%20AI%20could%20pose%20a%20threat%20to%20privacy.%3C%2F