%20though%20the%20state%20only%20mandates%20an%20inspection%20once%20every%20three%20years%2C%20she%20was%20easily%20able%20to%20locate%20several%20facilities%20that%20hadn't%20been%20inspected%20since%20before%20the%20COVID-19%20pandemic.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInspired%20by%20Morin's%20video%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fusafacts.org%2Fdata-projects%2Fchildcare-inspections%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eresearchers%20at%20USAFacts%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20not-for-profit%20group%20owned%20by%20current%20Los%20Angeles%20Clippers%20owner%20and%20former%20Microsoft%20Executive%20Steve%20Ballmer%2C%20compiled%20inspection%20data%20from%20148%2C166%20licensed%20childcare%20facilities%20in%2041%20states%20between%20June%20and%20September%202023%20to%20discover%20that%2014%2C683%20licensed%20childcare%20facilities%20across%20the%20country%20are%20behind%20on%20receiving%20their%20state-mandated%20inspections.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20is%20a%20national%20crisis%2C%20this%20is%20an%20issue%2C%26quot%3B%20Morin%20said%20to%20Insider%20after%20reviewing%20the%20new%20report.%20%26quot%3BParents%20trust%20the%20licensing%20department%20to%20do%20their%20job%2C%20and%20there's%20no%20jobs%20being%20done.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221934%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22USAFacts%20frequency%20chart%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F652ed986211def8ed8377bad%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224222%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EUSAFacts%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20federally-operated%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fchildcare.gov%2Fconsumer-education%2Fchild-care-licensing-and-regulations%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EChildCare.gov%3C%2Fa%3E%20website%2C%20licensing%20ensures%20that%20childcare%20facilities%20follow%20a%20minimum%20set%20of%20standards%20toward%20sanitation%2C%20child-to-caregiver%20ratio%2C%20building%20safety%2C%20and%20more.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20some%20states%20were%20wildly%20more%20out%20of%20compliance%20than%20others%20%E2%80%94%20only%2046%25%20of%20licensed%20childcare%20facilities%20in%20Idaho%20have%20reportedly%20received%20inspections%20compared%20to%2097%25%20of%20facilities%20in%20Ohio%20%E2%80%94%20overall%2C%20the%20report%20found%20that%20just%20under%2010%25%20of%20facilities%20were%20in%20need%20of%20one%2C%20according%20to%20each%20state's%20licensing%20rules%20and%20regulations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20for%20Minnesota%2C%20its%20state%20records%20reflect%20that%2085%25%20of%20its%20childcare%20facilities%20have%20received%20an%20inspection%20recently%20enough%20to%20comply%20with%20state%20law.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20USAFacts%20initially%20compiled%20the%20state's%20records%20just%20over%20a%20month%20ago%2C%20its%20report%20estimated%20that%2081%25%20of%20Minnesota's%20licensed%20childcare%20facilities%20were%20out%20of%20compliance%20%E2%80%94%20easily%20amounting%20to%20the%20largest%20proportion%20in%20the%20nation.%20The%20state%2C%20however%2C%20updated%20its%20public-facing%20records%20in%20recent%20weeks%20following%20several%20messages%20from%20Insider%20and%20USAFacts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20statement%20on%20Tuesday%2C%20a%20representative%20from%20the%20Minnesota%20Department%20of%20Human%20Services%20sent%20Insider%20data%20saying%20the%20proportion%20of%20licensed%20childcare%20facilities%20that%20had%20received%20inspections%20in%202022%20was%20over%2090%25%2C%20however%2C%20they%20noted%20they%20calculated%20their%20proportions%20using%20a%20calendar-year%20system%20while%20USAFacts'%20methodology%20instead%20pertained%20to%20the%20previous%20365%20days%2C%20which%20could%20account%20for%20the%20calculation%20differences.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20it%20comes%20to%20the%20frequency%20of%20required%20inspections%2C%20that%20varies%20from%20state%20to%20state.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.tn.gov%2Fhumanservices%2Ffor-families%2Fchild-care-services%2Fchild-care-rules-and-regulations.html%23%3A~%3Atext%3DTennessee%2527s%2520licensed%2520child%2520care%2520agencies%2Ccontinue%2520to%2520meet%2520licensing%2520requirements.%5C%22%3ETennessee%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20for%20example%2C%20requires%20childcare%20facilities%20to%20be%20inspected%20four%20times%20a%20year%2C%20while%20California%20only%20requires%20it%20once%20every%20three%20years.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221864%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22USAFacts%20table%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F652ed9b2be9edfa8eda30edc%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224364%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EUSAFacts%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20data%20visualization%20engineer%20at%20USAFacts%20who%20spearheaded%20the%20project%2C%20Amber%20Thomas%2C%20pointed%20out%20that%20her%20team%20discovered%20that%20about%2043%25%20of%20inspections%20resulted%20in%20the%20inspector%20discovering%20the%20childcare%20facility%20was%20out%20of%20compliance%20in%20some%20fashion.%20It's%20difficult%20in%20many%20cases%20to%20determine%20the%20specific%20violations%20found%20by%20the%20inspectors%20as%20they're%20not%20always%20listed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20can't%20say%20anything%20as%20to%20how%20severe%20that%20issue%20is%20because%20they%20didn't%20report%20how%20severe%20the%20issue%20is%2C%26quot%3B%20Thomas%20said.%20%26quot%3BSo%20it%20might%20just%20be%20your%20first%20aid%20kit%20is%20missing%20gauze.%20It%20might%20be%20your%20paperwork%20is%20a%20little%20bit%20out%20of%20date.%20It%20could%20be%20that%20you've%20got%20something%20super%20dangerous%20like%20guns%20in%20the%20house.%20But%20there's%20no%20way%20to%20know%20the%20difference%20between%20those%20things%20based%20on%20the%20data%20that%20they've%20provided.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDr.%20Katherine%20Glenn-Applegate%2C%20the%20director%20of%20child%20care%20and%20education%20initiatives%20at%20the%20Ohio-based%20childcare%20referral%20agency%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.actionforchildren.org%2F%5C%22%3EAction%20for%20Children%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20advised%20parents%20looking%20into%20childcare%20for%20their%20kids%20to%20do%20as%20much%20research%20as%20they%20can.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20would%20encourage%20parents%20to%20keep%20that%20in%20mind%20too%2C%20to%20do%20their%20research%20and%20be%20informed%20about%20the%20circumstances%20that%20their%20children%20are%20in%2C%20but%20know%20that%20there's%20a%20wide%20range%20of%20what%20the%20licensing%20violations%20might%20be.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20case%20of%20Morin's%20son's%20childcare%20facility%2C%20prior%20state%20inspections%20had%20already%20flagged%20it%20repeatedly%20for%20grossly%20violating%20the%20child-to-caregiver%20ratios.%20Each%20time%20that%20occurred%2C%20however%2C%20the%20facility's%20owner%20would%20close%20down%20the%20house-based%20daycare%20and%20start%20a%20new%20daycare%20at%20a%20separate%20location.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMorin%20alleged%20this%20was%20an%20intentional%20move%20by%20the%20facility%20owner%20to%20obfuscate%20their%20violations%20to%20parents%2C%20explaining%20that%20in%20California%20law%2C%20%26quot%3Blicense%20follows%20the%20address%2C%26quot%3B%20meaning%20that%20once%20a%20childcare%20facility%20changes%20its%20location%2C%20its%20history%20of%20violations%20doesn't%20follow%20alongside%20it%20in%20future%20reports%2C%20effectively%20wiping%20the%20slate%20clean.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENow%2C%20about%20seven%20years%20after%20Deacon's%20death%2C%20Morin%20frequently%20produces%20videos%20to%20her%20following%20of%20nearly%20700%2C000%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.tiktok.com%2F%40danimorin13%3Flang%3Den%5C%22%3ETikTok%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20her%20very%20own%20%26quot%3BMom%20hacks%2C%26quot%3B%20child-safety%20lessons%2C%20and%20tips%20on%20how%20to%20look%20into%20childcare%20facilities%20as%20she%20parents%20her%20son%2C%20Rhett.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAll%20I%20can%20do%20is%20share%20my%20story%20and%20tell%20people%2C%20'This%20is%20how%20I%20got%20bamboozled.%20Don't%20let%20it%20happen%20to%20you.%20Look%20into%20your%20childcare.'%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUSAFacts'%20report%20analyzed%20licensing%20data%20from%2041%20states%2C%20ultimately%20choosing%20to%20exclude%20Hawaii%2C%20Illinois%2C%20West%20Virginia%2C%20New%20Hampshire%2C%20Florida%2C%20Kansas%2C%20Massachusetts%2C%20Nebraska%2C%20and%20Pennsylvania%20from%20the%20report%20as%20its%20researchers%20were%20either%20unable%20to%20obtain%20any%20information%20due%20to%20technical%20and%20data%20limitations%20from%20the%20sources%20themselves%2C%20or%20were%20severely%20limited%20in%20the%20information%20provided%20by%20the%20states.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERepresentatives%20from%20the%20Ohio%20Department%20of%20Job%20and%20Family%20Services%20and%20California's%20Department%20of%20Social%20Services%20did%20not%20respond%20to%20Insider's%20request%20in%20time%20for%20publication.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchildcare-centers-are-behind-on-inspections-2023-10%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1697601602000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F652d48ee8bed706e837d2b7e%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchildcare-centers-are-behind-on-inspections-2023-10%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22In%20California%2C%20there%20are%20many%20licensed%20childcare%20facilities%20that%20haven't%20been%20inspected%20since%202019%20or%20even%202018%2C%20before%20the%20COVID-19%20pandemic%20began.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22mhall%40businessinsider.com%20(Madison%20Hall)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A18%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchildcare-centers-are-behind-on-inspections-2023-10%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%