%20And%20they%20have%20said%20that%20they%20will%20work%20together%20with%20us%20to%20find%20a%20way%20forward%20on%20this%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20Maldives%20is%20currently%20going%20through%20a%20transition%20period%2C%20with%20Muizzu%E2%80%99s%20term%20set%20to%20start%20on%20November%2017%20with%20a%20formal%20swearing-in%20ceremony.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAsked%20when%20he%20would%20request%20India%20to%20remove%20the%20troops%2C%20he%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CDefinitely%20day%20one.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ETo%20a%20follow-up%20question%20on%20the%20timeline%20for%20the%20withdrawal%20of%20troops%2C%20Muizzu%20replied%2C%20%E2%80%9C%E2%80%A6if%20it%20is%20possible%20within%20the%20first%20week%2C%20that%E2%80%99s%20how%20serious%20for%20us%20it%20is%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20that%20there%20were%20serious%20doubts%20about%20Maldives%E2%80%99s%20independence%20if%20foreign%20troops%20were%20stationed%20on%20its%20territory.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20have%20been%20a%20very%20peaceful%20country%20for%20centuries.%20We%20never%20had%20any%20foreign%20troops%20on%20our%20soil.%20We%20are%20a%20very%20small%20country.%20We%20do%20not%20have%20a%20big%20military%20set%20up%20and%20any%20foreign%20troops%20seen%20on%20our%20soil%2C%20we%20don%E2%80%99t%20feel%20ourselves%20secure%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20president-elect%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20Solih%20administration%20had%20repeatedly%20stated%20that%20there%20was%20no%20military%20operation%20by%20Indian%20troops%20and%20that%20only%20some%20security%20personnel%20were%20stationed%20to%20operate%20donated%20helicopters%20for%20medical%20evacuation.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20controversy%20over%20the%20alleged%20presence%20of%20Indian%20troops%20was%20first%20raked%20up%20by%20PPM%20leader%20Abdulla%20Yameen%20during%20the%20last%20few%20months%20of%20his%20presidency.%20India%20objected%20to%20President%20Yameen%E2%80%99s%20demand%20for%20withdrawal%2C%20but%20he%20was%20soon%20ousted%20in%20the%202019%20elections.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2018%2F11%2F18113701%2Fmodi-solih-2.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2018%2F11%2F18113701%2Fmodi-solih-2.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2018%2F11%2F18113701%2Fmodi-solih-2-300x200.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2018%2F11%2F18113701%2Fmodi-solih-2-1024x683.jpg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-312166%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22800%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EMaldives%20president%20Ibrahim%20Mohamed%20Solih%20and%20Indian%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi.%20Credit%3A%20Maldives%20government%20website%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CPresident%20Ibrahim%20Mohamed%20Solih%20has%20agreed%20about%20Indian%20military%20presence%2C%20but%20he%20did%20not%20disclose%20the%20nature%20of%20this%20presence%20because%20of%20which%20the%20citizens%20no%20longer%20wish%20for%20them%20to%20remain%20in%20Maldives%20any%20longer.%20That%20is%20also%20the%20reason%20why%20the%20public%20did%20not%20choose%20the%20current%20administration%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20the%20new%20president-elect.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHe%20also%20that%20there%20were%20conflicting%20reports%20about%20the%20numbers%20%E2%80%93%20ranging%20from%20thousands%20to%20hundreds%20%E2%80%93%20of%20Indian%20troops%20stationed%20in%20Maldives.%20%E2%80%9CWe%20don%E2%80%99t%20%5Bknow%5D%20how%20many%20are%20here%E2%80%A6%20Because%20when%20the%20media%20asks%20for%20information%2C%20it%20is%20censored%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EMuizzu%20hoped%20that%20when%20took%20over%20the%20presidency%2C%20the%20number%20of%20Indian%20troops%20would%20only%20be%20%E2%80%9C10%20or%2020%E2%80%9D%2C%20but%20added%20that%20even%20that%20would%20not%20be%20low%20enough.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CI%20will%20make%20sure%20that%20we%20find%20a%20way%20to%20talk%20diplomatically%20with%20the%20Indian%20government%20to%20remove%20them%20from%20our%20soil%20as%20soon%20as%20we%20can%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20told%20Al%20Jazeera.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ETo%20another%20question%20about%20general%20military%20cooperation%20with%20India%2C%20he%20indicated%20that%20it%20would%20continue%2C%20saying%2C%20%E2%80%9CMilitary%20cooperation%20has%20always%20been%20there%20with%20different%20countries.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20he%20wouldn%E2%80%99t%20like%20to%20increase%20military%20cooperation%20with%20China%20to%20balance%20with%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ENoting%20that%20half%20of%20Maldives%E2%80%99s%20external%20debt%20was%20from%20Indian%20borrowed%20loans%2C%20Muizzu%20said%20that%20he%20had%20also%20raised%20it%20with%20the%20Indian%20envoy%2C%20who%20had%20been%20positive%20about%20it.%20%E2%80%9CWe%20need%20a%20way%20to%20refinance%20and%20if%20possible%20waive%20(it%20off)%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWhen%20asked%20whether%20India%20would%20have%20any%20incentive%20to%20remove%20foreign%20troops%20when%20the%20Maldives%20was%20asking%20for%20debt%20waiver%2C%20Muizzu%20replied%2C%20%E2%80%9CThey%20have%20clearly%20said%20that%20in%20the%20very%20first%20meeting%20that%20I%20had%20with%20the%20high%20commissioner.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHe%20also%20stated%20that%20India%20didn%E2%80%99t%20seem%20inclined%20to%20diminish%20its%20development%20assistance%20or%20investment%20in%20the%20Indian%20Ocean%20state.%20%E2%80%9CI%20really%20don%E2%80%99t%20think%20they%20will%20do%20that.%20They%20may%20be%20interested%20in%20giving%20more%20lines%20of%20credit%20to%20invest%20in%20the%20tourism%20sector.%E2%80%9D%20Muizzu%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EStating%20that%20the%20Maldives%20always%20had%20a%20good%20relationship%20with%20India%2C%20he%20added%2C%20%E2%80%9CI%20don%E2%80%99t%20want%20it%20to%20be%20any%20different.%20It%20is%20only%20the%20sovereignty%20issue%E2%80%A6%20I%20will%20definitely%20be%20positive%20towards%20development%20assistance%20from%20India.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHe%20also%20that%20Maldives%20would%20also%20like%20to%20have%20close%20ties%20with%20China%20as%20with%20all%20other%20countries%2C%20but%20also%20noted%20that%20Beijing%20never%20extended%20its%20assistance%20in%20a%20way%20that%20would%20interfere%20in%20the%20internal%20affairs%20or%20impact%20the%20sovereignty%20of%20Maldives.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EEarlier%2C%20the%20Indian%20Ministry%20of%20External%20Affairs%20had%20talked%20about%20the%20need%20to%20work%20closely%20on%20security%20challenges%20after%20Muizzu%20raised%20the%20issue%20of%20Indian%20troops.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CAll%20I%20would%20say%E2%80%A6%20the%20focus%20of%20our%20partnership%20with%20the%20Maldives%20has%20always%20been%20on%20capacity%20building%20and%20working%20together%20to%20address%20our%20shared%20challenges%20and%20priorities%2C%20including%20security%20challenges%20and%20priorities.%20As%20neighbours%2C%20we%20need%20to%20collaborate%20closely%20to%20address%20these%20challenges%20confronting%20our%20region%2C%20such%20as%20transnational%20crimes%20and%20Humanitarian%20and%20Disaster%20Relief%20situations.%20We%20look%20forward%20to%20engaging%20with%20the%20new%20administration%20in%20the%20Maldives%20with%20all%20these%20issues%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20the%20MEA%20spokesperson%20at%20a%20media%20briefing%20on%20October%205.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1697554249000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F17194015%2FF8cxCy0agAA1r64.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fsouth-asia%2Fmaldives-mohamed-muizzu-indian-troops-top-priority%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Mohamed%20Muizzu%20told%20Al%20Ja